tmux cheat sheet in below website
https://tmuxcheatsheet.com/

Understand the hierarchy of tmux
Session
	windows
		pane

1 session can have multiple windows, and 1 window can have multiple panes

Binding h,j,k,l to resize the pane in your windows.
run below command from the shell before starting tmux or put it in the tmux config file 
--> tmux bind-key -n C-h resize-pane -L 1 # resize pane to the left 1 pixels with control-h
--> tmux bind-key -n C-l resize-pane -R 1 # resize pane to the left 1 pixels with control-l
--> tmux bind-key -n C-k resize-pane -U 1 # resize pane to the left 1 pixels with control-k
--> tmux bind-key -n C-j resize-pane -D 1 # resize pane to the left 1 pixels with control-j
